<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Buthelezi Says Millions of Zulus Not To Vote </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB2602191294 Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network in Afrikaans 
1600 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2602191294 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Afrikaans </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Inkatha Freedom party leader Mangosuthu Buthelezi 
said millions of King Zwelithini's followers will not take part 
in the elections unless demands for a Zulu kingdom are met. Dr. 
Buthelezi and King Goodwill today held talks in Ulundi with 
Minister of Home Affairs Danie Schutte. 
  [Begin recording] [Schutte, in English] From our side I can 
just say that the government is committed to an honorable 
recognition for the position of the Zulu king and kingdom in the 
new constitutional dispensation. There are restrictions and 
limitations but we are committed to that, and we will do 
everything in our power to try and bring that about. 
  [Buthelezi, in English] We don't think that it's a matter 
that's impossible to resolve as such because kingdoms exist in 
Africa. There was a kingdom in Uganda -- I think there are four 
kingdoms in Uganda, including the most (?northern) part of 
Uganda. Kingdoms have been accommodated in the colonialization 
period in Africa. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

