<H3> <TI>   Resignation of State Control Minister Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AB2702133094 Libreville RTG Chaine Nationale Radio Network 
in French 1200 GMT 27 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AB2702133094 </F>
<F P=104>  Libreville RTG Chaine Nationale Radio Network 
in French 1200 GMT 27 Feb 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] (Paul Bi Ogemba), a member of the National Assembly, 
the government, and the Gabonese Democratic Party [PDG], has 
just made a surprising statement in which he says he disagrees 
with the policies of President Omar Bongo and of the PDG. He 
forwarded two letters to the president of the Republic and to 
the PDG general secretary. (Paul Bi Ogemba) was minister of 
state control in charge of parastatal reforms. 

