  [Excerpt] A cabinet meeting was held on 25 February to 
review the state of the nation at month's end. The meeting was 
presided over by Mr. Faustin Birindwa, prime minister and head 
of government. The meeting began with a wide overview of the 
general national situation, and observed that general calm 
prevailed over the entire, vast national territory. 
