<H3> <TI>   Detained Opposition Leaders Could Face Death Penalty </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AB2702090094 London BBC World Service in English 0600 GMT 27 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AB2702090094 </F>
<F P=104>  London BBC World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "African News" program] </F>
  [Text] The authorities in Senegal have said the four 
opposition leaders charged after last week's disturbances in the 
capital, Dakar, could face death penalty. A statement from the 
attorney general's office said the maximum penalty could be 
applied if the men were found guilty of inciting the violence in 
which six policemen and two demonstrators were killed. The 
opposition leaders, Abdoulaye Wade, Landing Savane, (Boka Kane), 
and (Babacar Sane), have been charged with undermining state 
security. 

</TEXT>

