<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   ANC Objects to Right-Wing Military Training in N. Natal </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB0103120494 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1142 GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB0103120494 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cape Town March 1 SAPA -- Between 500 and 1,000 
people were being trained and armed in Northern Natal every 
fortnight, ANC [African National Congress] Secretary General 
Cyril Ramaphosa, told the Transitional Executive Committee on 
Tuesday. He said people in the Umfolozi area were being armed by 
white conservative farmers who were assisting in training them. 
  The only objective could be to serve the stated goal by 
certain parties that there would be no election allowed in the 
territory. "The activities clearly show something is afoot in 
preparing a number of people who are fully armed, probably to 
launch an attack on people going to vote." 
  Mr Ramaphosa quoted from a letter received from a local 
chief 
in December. "It demonstrates the problems we will face in 
Natal," he said. Guns were being deployed throughout the 
territory. 

</TEXT>

