<H3> <TI>   UNITA's Valentim: Government Lacks Seriousness </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB0103063194 Jamba Voz da Resistencia do Galo Negro in 
Portuguese 0600 GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0103063194 </F>
<F P=104>  Jamba Voz da Resistencia do Galo Negro </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The search for peace continues in the Zambian 
capital. The peace talks are to continue today with a second 
reading of the general document on national reconciliation that 
has been presented by the mediators. The National Union for the 
Total Independence of Angola [UNITA] and government teams held a 
plenary meeting yesterday, but no one knows what kind of 
progress may have been made. 
  Meanwhile, UNITA Information Secretary Dr. Jorge Alicerces 
Valentim yesterday accused the Luanda Government of lacking 
seriousness in its approach to the national reconciliation 
dossier. Speaking to a Portuguese radio station, that UNITA 
official said that the central and provincial government posts 
Luanda intends to give UNITA amount to nothing more than a joke. 
UNITA has been asking for greater participation in the 
country's administrative organs as a [word indistinct] of its 
commitment to the Lusaka peace talks [words indistinct]. 

</TEXT>

