<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The University of Abuja has been closed down. That 
followed a violent demonstration by the students during which 
the vice chancellor's office and two vehicles belonging to the 
institution were set ablaze. Radio Nigeria correspondents who 
visited the university campus report that a detachment of 
security agents is being stationed there to maintain law and 
order. The students had embarked on demonstrations to press 
their demand for a clarification of the legal (?status of the 
institution). 

