<H3> <TI>   Government Reacts to UN Resolution on Confinement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB0303091994 Maputo Radio Mozambique Network in Portuguese 
0800 GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0303091994 </F>
<F P=104>  Maputo Radio Mozambique Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Mozambican Government has reiterated that it 
intends and is willing to have general elections by not later 
than October 1994 in line with the General Peace Accord 
timetable. That is according to NOTICIAS which cites a 
statement issued by the government. NOTICIAS says that is the 
first government reaction to the recent UN Security Council 
resolution on the Mozambican peace process. The statement says 
the apparent delay in the confinement of government troops is 
not in any way caused by political or logistical reasons. The 
UN Security Council resolution vigorously urged the government 
and the Mozambique National Resistance to speed up the 
confinement of troops, and asked the sides to begin demobilizing 
their forces. 

</TEXT>

