<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Denies Vice Presidency Offer </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB0303071294 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 0500 GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0303071294 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Dr. Mangosuthu Buthelezi has denied reports that Mr. 
Mandela has offered a post as vice president to ensure the IFP's 
[Inkatha Freedom Party] participation in the election. However, 
he confirmed that he and Mr. Mandela had discussed possible 
positions the IFP would be qualified for in the future 
government. 

</TEXT>

