<H3> <TI>   Ruling PDCI To Hold Extraordinary Congress </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AB0403143194 Abidjan FRATERNITE MATIN in French 4 Mar 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> AB0403143194 </F>
<F P=104>  Abidjan FRATERNITE MATIN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by Diaby Salif] </F>
  [Excerpt] Where is the Democratic Party of Cote d'Ivoire- 
African Democratic Rally [PDCI-RDA] heading to? What will its 
activists do with the legacy of their founding father, President 
Houphouet-Boigny? These crucial questions were raised by 
PDCI-RDA Secretary General Laurent Dona-Fologo at a meeting with 
members of the party's political bureau at the party house in 
Cocody yesterday afternoon. 
  This is the party's first meeting since the death of 
President Houphouet-Boigny. On the occasion, Mr. Dona-Fologo 
announced that the PDCI-RDA will hold its extraordinary congress 
in April as stipulated in Article 25 of the standing rules. The 
congress will focus on the vacant party chairmanship post and 
the need to fill that prestigious post. [passage omitted] 

