<F P=101> Zaire </F>
<H3> <TI>   Disturbances on Border With Sudan Denied </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AB0703160094 Kinshasa Tele-Zaire Television Network in 
French 1230 GMT 6 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AB0703160094 </F>
<F P=104>  Kinshasa Tele-Zaire Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Prime Minister Faustin Birindwa yesterday 
presided over the weekly cabinet meeting. [passage omitted] On 
the state of the nation, the cabinet observed that there is 
effective calm throughout the whole country. The cabinet 
however condemned the fallacious statement made by a politician 
to the effect that there are disturbances in the northwestern 
part of the country. Contrary to that politician's false 
allegation, the government asserts that there is no detachment 
of the Special Presidential Division in that part of the country 
or a disturbing presence of the Sudanese Army on the Sudan-Zaire 
border. 
  The government deplores the fact that at the time when all 
Zairians are awaiting definite solutions to our problems from 
the Palais du Peuple, some fellow citizens in search of the 
sensational are taking the liberty to sow doubt in the minds of 
the people for unavowed reasons, and are systematically deriding 
our Armed Forces with outrageous statements. 
  In the face of such culpable irresponsibility, the 
government 
wishes to remind everyone that henceforth any statement 
discrediting our Armed Forces will be punished with the 
strongest force. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

