<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mangope Walks Out of Meeting </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB0703170594 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 1400 GMT 7 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0703170594 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hopes of a speedy end to a strike by public servants 
in Bophuthatswana were dashed today when President Lucas Mangope 
walked out of a crisis meeting aimed at resolving the issue. 
President Mangope called on the striking workers to outline 
their problems, but they insisted that he should address them 
first. 
  The strike, which has paralyzed most of the essential 
services in the territory, has resulted in cancellations at the 
many luxury hotels in the area, and Sun City has admitted that 
it is being badly affected. 
  One of the demands by the strikers is the reincorporation of 
Bophuthatswana into South Africa. Earlier today the 
Bophuthatswana cabinet decided that the territory would not take 
part in the election. 

</TEXT>

