<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   MP Resigns From National Party, Joins Inkatha </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB0703142394 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1329 GMT 7 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB0703142394 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By Dirk van Zyl] </F>
  [Text] Cape Town March 7 SAPA -- The Inkatha Freedom Party 
[IFP] gained its fourteenth MP on Monday when James Kuiler, MP 
for Manenberg, announced his resignation from the National Party 
[NP]. Mr Kuiler entered the House of Representatives in 1989 as 
a Labour Party MP, and in 1991 joined the NP. The IFP now has 
five members in the House of Assembly, seven in the House of 
Delegates and two in the House of Representatives. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

