<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Gazankulu Chief Withdraws Party From Election </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB0503174794 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 1600 GMT 5 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0503174794 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Gazankulu chief minister, Chief Nxumalo, has 
withdrawn the Ximoko Progressive Party from the election. 
Speaking at Giyani, the chief said the split in the party had 
left him with no choice but to align himself with the ANC 
[African National Congress]. The chief was suspended as 
president of the party at a congress of another faction of the 
party last weekend. 

</TEXT>

