<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   ANC Not Likely To Move Parliament From Cape Town </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB0703064494 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 0500 GMT 7 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0703064494 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The ANC [African National Congress] says there is 
little likelihood that Parliament will be moved from Cape Town 
in the foreseeable future. The head of the department of 
information and publicity in the Western Cape, Mr. Bulelani 
Ngcuka, and parliamentary candidate Jay Naidoo told a news 
conference that building another parliament would be a waste of 
resources. They said the ANC's priorities were jobs, housing, 
electricity, and health services, not putting up new public 
buildings. 

</TEXT>

