<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   50 Light Weapons Stolen </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB0803140994 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1009 GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB0803140994 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pretoria March 8 SAPA -- About 50 light weapons had 
been stolen from the Air Force's 10 Air Depot, Air Force 
Headquarters said in a statement on Tuesday [8 March]. It was 
suspected three or four people were involved in the weekend 
burglary which was discovered on Monday morning. Air Force 
police and the South African Police [SAP] were immediately 
called in to investigate, the statement said, but the SAP on 
Tuesday denied it was involved in the investigation. The Air 
Force said further details could not be released at this stage 
because it could hamper the investigation. 

</TEXT>

