<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Peacekeeping Force Reports 117 Members Resign </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB0703155494 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 1400 GMT 7 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0703155494 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] One-hundred-seventeen members of the National 
Peacekeeping Force receiving training at the General De Wet 
training center outside Bloemfontein have resigned since the 
start of the weekend. A spokesman for the force said that 
reasons for the resignations varied from domestic problems to 
dissatisfaction with conditions at the base. 
  About 70 members of the force resigned last week after a 
strike over salaries. However, the spokesman said that 
conditions at the base had returned to normal and that training 
had been resumed. He said a delegation from the Transitional 
Executive Council would visit the base this afternoon to help 
solve the problem. 

</TEXT>

