<H3> <TI>   Portuguese Minister Warns of Potential for Civil War </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB0403155294 Johannesburg Afrikaans Stereo Radio Network in 
Afrikaans 1400 GMT 4 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0403155294 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Afrikaans Stereo Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Afrikaans </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Portuguese foreign minister, Dr. Jose Manuel 
Barroso, has warned that there is not much time left for an 
all-inclusive political settlement in South Africa and that 
there's potential for civil conflict if this fails. He was 
addressing a news conference in Johannesburg after meeting CP 
[Conservative Party] leader, Dr. Ferdi Hartzenberg. Dr. Barroso 
said that he had urged Dr. Hartzenberg to be flexible and to 
consider participation in the election. 
  Dr. Barroso, who is on a visit to South Africa, is to meet 
Afrikaner Volksfront [Afrikaner National Front] leader Constand 
Viljoen later today. 

</TEXT>

