<H3> <TI>   Government Signs Cooperation Agreement With Russia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB0703131294 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 1100 GMT 7 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0703131294 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] South Africa and Russia have signed an agreement 
providing for closer cooperation in the areas of labor and 
social relations. Speaking at the ceremony in Pretoria, 
Manpower Minister Leon Wessels said that South Africa had 
survived a protracted period of isolationism, however, now that 
doors were opening to the country, it was becoming clear that it 
needed to make up lost time. The Russian-South African 
agreement, he said, would enable the two countries to exchange 
knowledge and expertise. 

</TEXT>

