<F P=102>  MB0503174994 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 1600 GMT 5 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0503174994 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Vatican and South Africa have established full 
diplomatic relations. The Vatican said the move would make it 
easier for Pope John Paul, who often condemned apartheid, to 
visit the country. The pope is due to make a trip to Africa 
late this year or early next year. 

