<H3> <TI>   After Delay, Transitional Government Sworn In </TI></H3>
<H4>   ULIMO Blocks NPRA Delegation </H4>
<F P=102> AB0703125194 Gbarnga Radio ELRL in English 1212 GMT 7 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AB0703125194 </F>
<F P=104>  Gbarnga Radio ELRL </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] We would like to inform our many listeners and the 
public that the delegation headed by Vice President Enoch 
Dogolee from the NPRAG [National Patriotic Reconstruction 
Assembly Government]-controlled areas to Monrovia, we 
understand, is being delayed right now in Kakata, where in fact, 
ULIMO [United Liberation Movement for Democracy in Liberia] is 
controlling. There is no reason given as to how the delay has 
been like. 

</TEXT>

