<F P=101> Liberia </F>
<H3> <TI>   After Delay, Transitional Government Sworn In </TI></H3>
<H4>   Kpomakpor Urges Rebuilding Effort </H4>
<F P=102> AB0803121394 Monrovia Radio ELBC in English 0900 GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AB0803121394 </F>
<F P=104>  Monrovia Radio ELBC </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The chairman of the State Council of the Liberia 
National Transitional Government, Counselor David Kpomakpor, has 
called on Liberians to reunite and rebuild a peaceful and 
(?prosperous nation). Chairman Kpomakpor made the call 
yesterday in an inaugural address delivered shortly after his 
induction as the chairman of the council. He said the task of 
rebuilding Liberia is an enormous one but said that it could be 
done once all Liberians are willing and committed in rebuilding 
their country. He expressed his deep appreciation to the ECOWAS 
[Economic Community of West African States] and the entire 
international community for their assistance to Liberia in its 
hour of need and pledged the council's commitment to an upright, 
(?democratic) government. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

