<F P=101> Nigeria </F>
<H3> <TI>   Army Spokesman Reasserts Claim to Bakassi </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AB0703124094 Lagos Voice of Nigeria in English 1030 GMT 7 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AB0703124094 </F>
<F P=104>  Lagos Voice of Nigeria </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Brigadier General Fred Chijuka, the director of 
Nigeria's defense information, has reasserted Nigeria's claim to 
the Bakassi Peninsula. He said that the peninsula, including 
its eastern part of (?Zabari), had been part of Nigerian 
territory since 1914 and will remain so. 
  Speaking on a Voice of Nigeria interview, Brig. Gen. Chijuka 
said the territory which Cameroonians are also claiming, was 
handed over to Nigeria at independence by the British who 
themselves had controlled the area since their 1914 agreement 
with the French. He said that because of its brotherly attitude 
towards its neighbors, Nigeria has consistently refused to be 
provoked by the incessant crossborder harassments by Cameroon, 
some of which had resulted in the loss of Nigerian lives. The 
defense information director said Cameroon had not reciprocated 
Nigeria's good neighborliness and so Nigeria now had a prime 
objective to assert its presence in the peninsula and make all 
know that the area belongs to it. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

