<F P=101> Kenya </F>
<H3> <TI>   Saudi Airlines Plane Hijacked To Nairobi </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AB0803092394 Paris AFP in English 0906 GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AB0803092394 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Nairobi, 8 March (AFP) -- A Saudi Arabian Airlines 
plane was hijacked early Tuesday [8 March] on a flight between 
Addis Ababa and Jiddah and made an emergency landing here, the 
Saudi Airlines office in the Kenyan capital said. All 159 
passengers were allowed to leave the plane, an Airbus, after it 
landed around 4:30 A.M. (0130 GMT) and only two crew members 
remained on board, the captain and his co-pilot, the spokesman 
said. The passengers, almost of whom were Ethiopian, were safe, 
he said. 
  There were thought to be three or four hijackers, according 
to the spokesman. He said airport officials were negotiating 
with the hijackers, but gave no official details on their 
demands. But an unofficial source at Jomo Kenyatta Airport said 
the hijackers were demanding to fly to Italy and told airport 
officials to re-fuel the plan. The Saudi ambassador to Nairobi 
had rushed to the scene, the Saudi Embassy here said, but gave 
no other information. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

