<F P=100> EAST AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Kenya </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further on Hijacking </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AB0803120794 Nairobi KTN Television Network in English 1000 
GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AB0803120794 </F>
<F P=104>  Nairobi KTN Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A Saudi airliner was this morning hijacked to 
Nairobi. The plane is said to have landed at the Jomo Kenyatta 
International Airport at 0400. Reports from the airport say 
that the crew and passengers were allowed to disembark and are 
being looked after in the VIP pavilion at the airport. 
Officials of the airline in Nairobi are reported to have 
refused to talk to the press. 
  A KTN reporter says that 130 Ethiopians were aboard the 
plane, an A-300/600 [as heard] Airbus. The Ethiopians were 
being deported from Jiddah to Addis Ababa. Also on board were 
nine international passengers. 
  Three hijackers are reported to have commandeered the airbus 
to Nairobi. One hijacker disembarked with the passengers, while 
the other two are reported to be still aboard the plane. The 
hijackers' nationalities were not immediately known. 

</TEXT>

