<H3> <TI>   Pakistani Troops Accused of Rights Violations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  EA0703202394 (Clandestine) Radio Mogadishu Voice of the 
Great Somali People in Somali 1700 GMT 7 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA0703202394 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Radio Mogadishu Voice of the 
Great Somali People </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Somali </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A spokesman for the Somali National Alliance [SNA] 
has said that Pakistani troops threw out wounded Somalis who had 
been admitted to their hospitals. The SNA spokesman described 
the move as the worst violation of human rights, adding that the 
Pakistani troops had previously committed such a violation. The 
spokesman added that some of the patients who had been ejected 
had died. He appealed to Somalis to take patients to Somali 
hospitals. 

</TEXT>

