<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bophuthatswana Quiet; No Sign of Alleged Coup </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB0803083194 Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network in English 0500 
GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB0803083194 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Bophuthatswana capital of Mmabatho was quiet 
overnight after another day of tension, with no signs of an 
alleged coup. Feelings ran high yesterday following a 
Bophuthatswana cabinet decision not to participate in the April 
election. The announcement came amid an already volatile 
situation as civil servants demanding reincorporation into South 
Africa continued their strike. At the Mmabatho Sun Hotel, which 
was occupied by disgruntled workers yesterday, it was business 
as usual, and by midnight last night all communication links had 
been restored. 

</TEXT>

