<H3> <TI>   Another 200 Italian Soldiers Leave Mogadishu </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0903115694 Rome RAI Due Television Network in Italian 1045 
GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0903115694 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Due Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Italian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Another 200 Italian soldiers have left Somalia. As 
the conclusion of the UN mandate approaches, all the 
international contingents are reducing their presence. Some 
1,000 Italian troops remain in Mogadishu. The demobilization of 
the UNOSOM [United Nations Operation in Somalia] troops is 
taking place in a climate of intense fighting between warring 
factions that are still a long way from reaching any peace 
settlement. 

